 <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="545">
  <subfield code="a">
   Dr. Benjamin J. Luft is the Edmund D. Pellegrino Professor of Medicine at the Stony Brook University and an internationally recognized expert in the treatment of Lyme disease and AIDS-related conditions. In 2001, Dr. Luft, a native New Yorker, responded to 9/11 as Chair of the Department of Medicine at the State University of New York at Stony Brook (Stony Brook University). He established a 9/11 clinical center, the Stoney Brook WTC Wellness Program for the 9/11 responder community, initiated an oral history project with 9/11 first responders, and has published a book and film and developed curriculum materials from these interviews.
  </subfield>
 </datafield>
